\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. L. sylvatica} (Hudson) Gaudin, {\i Agrost. Helv.}{\b  2}: 240 (1811). Plant (30-)40-80(-100) cm, robust, laxly caespitose, with numerous short, ascending stolons. Basal leaves 5-20(-30) mm wide, spreading, sparsely to densely ciliate. Flowers in groups of 2-5. Bracteoles conspicuously lacerate to ciliate. Perianth-segments 2-4(-4·5) mm, brown; inner longer than outer, with wide hyaline margin. Anthers up to 6 times as long as filaments. Style longer than ovary. Capsule about equalling the perianth-segments, ovoid. Seeds slightly shiny; basal appendage small. {\i Damp woods, moorland and rocky places; usually calcifuge. S., W. & C. Europe.} Al Au Be Br Bu Co Cz Da Fa Ga Ge Gr Hb He Ho Hs It Ju Lu No Po Rm Rs (W) Si Tu [Su].
