\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. L. sieberi} Tausch,{\i  Flora} ({\i Regensb.}) {\b 19}: 423 (1836). Plant (30-)40-60 cm, laxly caespitose. Basal leaves 3-6 mm wide, distinctly ciliate. Flowers borne 2-3 together. Perianth-segments 3-3·5(-4) mm, reddish-brown. Anthers longer than filaments. Style longer than ovary. Capsule 2·5-3(-3·5) mm, ovoid, equalling the perianth. Seeds 1·2-1·3 mm.{\i  Coniferous woods. • Alps; mountains of C. Jugoslavia.} Au Ge He It Ju.
