\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. L. nivea} (L.) DC. in Lam. & DC., {\i Fl. Fr.} ed. 3,{\b  3}: 158 (1805). Plant 40-60(-80) cm, laxly caespitose, with long stolons. Basal leaves 3-4(-5) mm wide, flat; cauline leaves 15-20 cm. Inflorescence with 6-20 flower-clusters; peduncles suberect to somewhat recurved. Perianth-segments c. 5 mm, whitish, unequal, acute. Anthers about as long as or shorter than filaments. Style longer than ovary. Capsule 2-2·5 mm, globose, c. ½ as long as perianth. Seeds c. 1·5 mm, reddish-brown. 2n = 12.{\i  Woodland and scrub, mainly in the mountains. • From N.C. France southwards to N.E. Spain, C. Italy and Slovenija.} Au Ga Ge He Hs It Ju ?Rm.
