\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 20. L. lactea} (Link) E.H.F. Meyer, {\i Syn. Luzul.} 15 (1823). Plants 30-60(-70) cm, laxly caespitose, with long stolons; stem rigid. Basal leaves c. 4 mm wide, with slightly revolute margins; cauline leaves 6-10 cm; leaf-sheaths soon decaying into a brownish fibrous mass. Inflorescence with 8-20 clusters, each cluster of 8-20(-30) flowers. Perianth-segments 4·5-5(-5·5) mm, equal, subobtuse or acuminate, whitish, translucent. Anthers up to twice as long as filaments. Style longer than ovary. Capsule c. 2 mm, ovoid, 1/3-1/2 as long as perianth-segments. Seeds 1·1-1·2 mm, reddish-brown; basal appendage inconspicuous. 2n = 12. {\i Woods, scrub, heaths and mountain meadows. • N. & C. Spain, N. Portugal; Açores.} Az Hs Lu.
