\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 21. L. pedemontana} Boiss. & Reuter,{\i  Pugillus} 115 (1852). Plant (25-)30-60 cm, caespitose, with short stolons. Basal leaves convolute; cauline leaves c. 2 mm wide, somewhat convolute to flat. Inflorescence lax, with (10-)20-40(-50) clusters, each with 2-3(-5) flowers. Perianth-segments (2·8-)3-3·3 mm, whitish, translucent, subequal. Anthers about twice as long as filaments. Style about twice as long as ovary. Capsule 2·8-3·2 mm, about as long as or slightly shorter than perianth-segments, oblong-ovoid. Seeds 1·2-1·5 mm, greyish-brown. {\i Open woods and scrub. • S.W. Alps, N. Appennini, Corse. }Co Ga It.
